<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - VALVE TRAIN: PUSH RODS ,
        HYDRAULIC VALVE LIFTERS AND CAMSHAFT - Push Rods and Hydraulic Valve Lifters - Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Assembly</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To avoid engine damage after assembly, perform a leak down test to ensure that leakage past the
                    plunger and lifter body is correct. This assures that the check valve is functioning properly.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1200608" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figcg1/CG11079.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="392px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Assembling the Valve Lifter</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Lifter Body with Roller</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Plunger Spring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Plunger</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Plunger Body</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Metering Valve</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Push Rod Seat</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Retainer</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat all hydraulic valve lifter parts with clean engine oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the plunger spring and plunger into the plunger body, then into the lifter body.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the metering valve and push rod seat into the valve lifter body. Secure the
                components with a retaining ring.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
